    "body": "### Problem\n\nStopping a language server and then calling `vim.lsp.start()` with the same name/root will return the old language server that's in the middle of shutting down. `vim.lsp.start()` won't return a new server until the old process has terminated.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\nlocal start_opts = { cmd = { 'npx', '-y', 'typescript-language-server', '--stdio' }, name = 'start-stop-test' }\nlocal client1 = vim.lsp.start(start_opts)\nvim.lsp.stop_client(client1)\nlocal client2 = vim.lsp.start(start_opts)\nprint('these should be different', client1, client2)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect a new client with a new id. The old client is unusable even if the process is still technically still running.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nany\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nany\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
